OL,3,CGisele Pelicot's ex-husband praises
OL,4,Cher courage in coming forward
OL,6,FHis co-defendants have done their best
OL,7,Fto stay hidden during this trial,
OL,8,Fwearing masks and hoods to walk in and
OL,9,Fout of court. Today only a handful
OL,10,Fchose to speak. Some offered an
OL,11,Fapology, but only two men turned to
OL,12,Faddress Gisele Pelicot directly.
OL,14,FIn contrast, their alleged victim
OL,15,Fsacrificed her right to privacy so
OL,16,Fthat the trial could be heard in
OL,17,Fpublic. After a trial lasting nearly
OL,18,Ffour months, her lawyer told me she is
OL,19,Fboth exhausted and relieved, but
OL,20,Fdoesn't regret her choice.
